.TH "drm_bus_flags_from_videomode" 9 "drm_bus_flags_from_videomode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_bus_flags_from_videomode \- extract information about pixelclk and DE polarity from videomode and store it in a separate variable
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_bus_flags_from_videomode
.BI "(const struct videomode *vm "  ","
.BI "u32 *bus_flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vm" 12
videomode structure to use
.IP "bus_flags" 12
information about pixelclk, sync and DE polarity will be stored
here
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sets DRM_BUS_FLAG_DE_(LOW|HIGH),  DRM_BUS_FLAG_PIXDATA_DRIVE_(POS|NEG)EDGE
and DISPLAY_FLAGS_SYNC_(POS|NEG)EDGE in \fIbus_flags\fP according to DISPLAY_FLAGS
found in \fIvm\fP
